HEADWORD: Pseudodox
<hw>Pseu"do*dox</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pseydo`doxos</grk>; <grk>pseydh`s</grk> false + <grk>do`xa</grk> an
opinion.]</ety> <def>Not true in opinion or doctrine; false.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A false opinion or doctrine.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To
maintain the atheistical <xex>pseudodox</xex> which judgeth evil good,
and darkness light.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>T. Adams.</au></rj> </def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudofilaria</ent>⟦br⟧
